                 #######################
                #########################
                ## TINY KERNEL LIBRARY ##
                #########################
                 #######################

The makefile contains all the targets you should ever need.
The targets are:
    - doc           Builds the Doxugen documentation
    - <no target>   Compiles the usage binary
    - debug         Compiles the usage binary (with debug flags)
    - optim         Compiles the usage binary (with optimization flags)
    - zip           Compresses the whole directory
    - clean         Removes all generated files and folders

A brief description follows.

#######
# doc #
#######

Execute
    user@pc$ make doc

This target calls Doxygen to create the documentation for the classes in the library.
A soft link called doc.html is created in the main folder. Use this to access the documentation.

###############
# <no target> #
###############

Execute
    user@pc$ make <no-target>

This target creates the bin folder and compiles the usage binary.

#########
# debug #
#########

Execute
    user@pc$ make debug

This target creates the bin folder and compiles the usage binary.
The compilation includes debugging flags.

#########
# optim #
#########

Execute
    user@pc$ make optim

This target creates the bin folder and compiles the usage binary.
The compilation includes optimization flags.

#######
# zip #
#######

Execute
    user@pc$ make zip

This target compresses the current folder _as is_ into TKL.zip.

#########
# clean #
#########

Execute
    user@pc$ make clean

This target removes all generated folders and files (which include bin/, doc/, doc.html, and others..)

